'''Ovide Musin''' (1854â€“1929) was a Belgian [[violinist]] and [[composer]].

== Life ==
Musin was born in [[Nandrin]], Belgium in 1854. He started learning violin at the age of six.<ref name="sarahplumviolinist">{{cite web|url=http://www.sarahplumviolinist.com/interactive_studio_details.php?id=34|title=Ovide Musin|publisher=sarahplumviolinist.com|accessdate=2015-11-16}}</ref>

In 1891, he married [[Annie Louise Tanner-Musin|Annie Louise Tanner]].<ref name="sarahplumviolinist"/>

He died in New York in the year 1929.<ref name="sarahplumviolinist"/>

== Career ==
In 1884, he gave his first concert in America. He then went on a tour of the United States in which he got to perform at many cities.<ref name="sarahplumviolinist"/>

In 1898, he returned to Belgium, where he was appointed as a professor at the Brussels conservatory where he himself had studied.<ref name="sarahplumviolinist"/>

== Bibliography ==
His autobiography, entitled ''My Memories,'' is an important source for his life and career.<ref name="sarahplumviolinist"/>

